#import "/_lib/0.1.1.typ": *
#show: template

#taxon[Definition]
#title[Integral morphism]

A morphism of schemes $pi : X ->  Y$ is _integral_ if it is affine and for every affine open set $"Spec"(B) subset Y$ with $pi^(-1) ("Spec"(B)) ~= "Spec"(A)$, the ring $A$ is an inegral extension of $B$ via $pi^hash$
